<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Doukyuusei 2 is a video game published by ELF and sequel to Dokyusei. Dokyusei 2 was released in 1995 in DOS version and in 1997 in Windows & Playstation versions.
                  <br><br>The player plays the role of a high school male student. In the winter vacation of the last school year (from 22 December to 7 January), he has to choose one girl to be his girlfriend. There are 15 choices for him to make, some are his classmates and some have to be met in the city. The player has to meet the girls and make friends with one of them until the relationship develops to a point that the girl is willing to become his girlfriend.
                  <br><br>CHARACTERS:
                  <br>* Narusawa Yui: A girl who calls Ryunosuke "elder brother" and who lives with him.
                  <br>* Mizuno Tomomi: A friend of Ryunosuke since they were children.
                  <br>* Shinohara Izumi: A good friend of Tomomi. Ryunosuke cannot become the boyfriend of Tomomi and Izumi at the same time.
                  <br>* Minamikawa Yoko: A girl who always quarrels with Ryunosuke.
                  <br>* Kato Minori: A girl who works in a tuckshop called "Hiroko".
                  <br>* Maijima Karen: A girl who seldom goes to school since she works as a super star.
                  <br>* Sugimoto Sakurako: A patient of the 88 Hospital.
                  <br><br>The following girls are not classmates of Ryunosuke:
                  <br>* Tsuzuki Kozue: A girl who is a schoolmate of Ryunosuke, two years his junior.
                  <br>* Narusawa Misako: The mother of Yui, she lives with Ryunosuke.
                  <br>* Nonomura Misato: A girl who works as a tour guide.
                  <br>* Yasuda Azumi: A girl who is a young baby-sitter.
                  <br>* Tanaka Misa: A girl who comes to Ryunosuke's town during vacation. Misa is also a returning character from the first Doukyuusei, being a fan favorite.
                  <br>* Nagashima Sachiko: The owner of the Nagashima hostel in Toji Onsen.
                  <br>* Nagashima Kumiko: The daughter of Sachiko, she wants to live in city instead of living in the countryside.
                  <br>* Katagari Mirei: The class teacher of Ryunosuke.
                  <br><br>Male characters in the game:
                  <br>* Saionji Aritomo: A classmate of Ryunosuke. He has a rich family, and his relationship with Ryunosuke is not so good.
                  <br>* Nagaoka Yoshiki: A classmate of Ryunosuke.
                  <br>* Kaojiri Akira: A classmate and good friend of Ryunosuke.
                  <br>* Tendo Shinkansen: The PE teacher of the 88 high school who always torture his students.
                  <br><br>The game features japanese voice acting for the characters and unlockable girls picture gallery and music room.
                  <br><br>This Limited Edition version was released in a box set which included a set of figures.				  
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Classmates ported the popular dating simulation sequel. Niatari porting from PC version, new graphics, as well as a wealth of additional factors such as the new episodes. Actors hired a luxury, excitement from the story. Set in high school last winter, make friends and memories of charming and heroines.
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>First person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Romance & Anime themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

